The optimal management of patients with asymptomatic carotid stenosis (ACS) is 
the subject of extensive debate. According to the 2017 European Society for 
Vascular Surgery Guidelines, carotid endarterectomy should (Class IIa; Level of 
Evidence: B) or carotid artery stenting may be considered (Class IIb; Level of 
Evidence: B) in the presence of one or more clinical/imaging characteristics 
